'''''Culture of Death''''' has two distinct meanings:
*a term used in contemporary political discourse in the [[United States]] to describe certain positions that contrast with a [[Culture of Life]].

*a term used in [[Imperialism|Colonial Europe]] to describe [[barbarian|"barbaric"]] cultures which allegedly glorified or worshiped death.  This was then used as a justification for the subjagation and colonization of these cultures.
